# Inefficient mobile use

## User issue
The user finds the product difficult to use on mobile.

## Possible causes
- Not a fully responsible design
- Buttons or interactive elements are too small
- Content does not fit on smaller screens
- CSS media queries are missing or not working completely

## Troubleshooting steps
1. Ask the user which device or browser they are using.
2. Ask the user which part of the page or feature is difficult to use.
3. Test - try to reproduce the issue on a similar device or screen size.
4. Check layout, responsiveness, and touch interactions.

